Content:
The Pavement Studios was formed in 2000 by Andy Evans, Lloyd Shaer and Kristen O'Sullivan based in Strongrom Studios in Shoreditch in the East End of London. The Pavement specialises in the production of DVD, Blu-ray, Blu-ray 3D and other entertainment platforms for TV, Film, Music, Children's and other genres. The Pavement has been responsible for many UK produced programmes brought to life on disc including: The League of Gentleman, Spaced, Shaun of the Dead, Hot Fuzz, Scott Pilgrim Vs. the World, U2360 Tour. 
